Analysis.name: Adverse effects (abdominal pain)
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc:
1. Women were equally randomised (1:1) to receive misoprostol or placebo. The Leiden University Medical Center pharmacist prepared the envelope and study medication. The study medication was provided in a single number coded container.

2. There were more nulliparous women in the misoprostol group (35/48 vs. 23/51, p = 0.003)

Analysis.name: Adverse effects (abdominal pain)
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc:
1. Study medication was randomised in blocks of 4, the allocation of sealed envelopes was in the sequence of enrolment.

2. No difference in obstetric data.
